title: bittalk7
author: bittalk7
content: Hello btc forum! One of my 5 s9 is being tricky for some reason. Back ground is I bought it used and it didnt work on nicehash correctly but it worked on btcpool correctly. Now here I am set up some new miners and was trying to bring it back to nicehash and I forgot to save the setting to log back into my btcpool account correctly. Can you give me an example of what it should look like in the pool setting. This is what I'm running now and its showing alive but its not showing up on the btcpool side as an active miner.us.ss.btc.com:1800antMiner7.001123SOFTWARE NOTE: Using hiveonkernel if it helps at all... comments.body: Quote from: bittalk7 on August 17, 2022, 08:19:00 PMthank you for updating me, I forget nicehash just pays you for hashing speed. I did solve this issue by creating a flight plan and wallet in hiveon.
